@startuml
title casbinjs/core - Usage, Delegation, and Synchronization Flow

skinparam shadowing false

actor ConsumerApp as Consumer
participant "External Endpoint" as Endpoint
box "casbinjs/core"
participant "Authorizer Facade" as Authorizer
participant "Policy Snapshot" as PolicySnapshot
participant "Enforcer Factory" as Factory
end box
box "casbin-core"
participant "Enforcer" as Enforcer
end box

== Initialization ==

Consumer -> Endpoint : fetch authorization data
Endpoint --> Consumer : policy snapshot
Consumer -> Authorizer : createAuthorizer(...)
Authorizer -> PolicySnapshot : initialize policy snapshot
Authorizer -> Factory : build / configure enforcer
Factory -> Enforcer : initialize with model / policies

== Permission checks ==

Consumer -> Authorizer : can(action, resource)
Authorizer -> Enforcer : enforce(subject, resource, optional scope, action)
Enforcer --> Authorizer : allow / deny
Authorizer --> Consumer : boolean

Consumer -> Authorizer : canAny(actions, resource)
loop each action
  Authorizer -> Enforcer : enforce(subject, resource, optional scope, action)
  Enforcer --> Authorizer : result
end
Authorizer --> Consumer : boolean

Consumer -> Authorizer : canAll(actions, resource)
loop each action
  Authorizer -> Enforcer : enforce(subject, resource, optional scope, action)
  Enforcer --> Authorizer : result
end
Authorizer --> Consumer : boolean

== Policy mutation ==

Consumer -> Authorizer : addPolicy(policy)
Authorizer -> PolicySnapshot : append policy row
Authorizer -> Enforcer : apply policy mutation

Consumer -> Authorizer : removePolicy(policy)
Authorizer -> PolicySnapshot : remove policy row
Authorizer -> Enforcer : apply policy removal

Consumer -> Authorizer : replacePolicies(policies)
Authorizer -> PolicySnapshot : replace full policy snapshot
Authorizer -> Enforcer : rebuild effective policies

== Consumer-owned backend sync ==

group Canonical policy snapshot refetch
  Consumer -> Endpoint : refetch policy snapshot
  Endpoint --> Consumer : updated policies
  Consumer -> Authorizer : replacePolicies(policies)
end

group Optimistic update with reconciliation
  Consumer -> Authorizer : removePolicy(policy)
  Authorizer -> PolicySnapshot : optimistic local removal
  Consumer -> Endpoint : persist mutation
  alt backend success
    Endpoint --> Consumer : canonical updated policies
    Consumer -> Authorizer : replacePolicies(policies)
  else backend failure
    Endpoint --> Consumer : canonical policies with original rule present
    Consumer -> Authorizer : replacePolicies(policies)
  end
end

note over Consumer,Endpoint
Outside library boundary.
casbinjs/core does not fetch or persist.
The consumer owns API integration.
end note

note over Authorizer,PolicySnapshot
replacePolicies(policies):
- replaces the full in-memory policy snapshot
- acts as canonical reconciliation input
end note

note over Enforcer
casbin-core owns:
- enforcement execution
- model evaluation
- policy processing
end note

note over Authorizer
organization is optional and acts as scope
when delegating enforcement.

Worker-backed execution may be added later,
but the initial core design remains in-process.
end note
@enduml
